Philippine Stocks: Lepanto, Philex Mining, Megaworld, Vista Land

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-06-13T04:53:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-13/banco-de-oro-cebu-air-metropolitan-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 1.1 percent to
4,171.54, the lowest level since April 5.  Property stocks:  Megaworld Corp. (MEG)  , a developer of
residential and office towers, fell 2.9 percent to 1.98 pesos,
the lowest close since May 26.  Vista Land & Lifescapes Inc. (VLL)   declined 2.2 percent to 3.12 pesos, the lowest level since
May 13.  Central bank Governor Amando Tetangco said inflation
pressures “still exist,” fueling concern the monetary
authority may raise  interest rates  at this week’s policy
meeting.  Mining companies:  Philex Mining Corp. (PX)  , the nation’s
largest metals producer, slid 2.7 percent to 19.10 pesos, the
lowest level since May 26. Class B shares of  Lepanto
Consolidated Mining (LCB)  Co slumped 9.4 percent to 97
centavos, the sharpest loss since May 13.  Gold for immediate delivery fell 0.7 percent last week,
while copper for three-month delivery in  London  dropped 1.8
percent. The declines were the sharpest weekly losses for both
commodities since May 6.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
